## üé® PRODUCTION DESIGN REQUIREMENTS

**Every concept must deliver:**

### Aesthetic Quality Standards
1. **Geometric Precision** - All curves smooth, angles exact, no hand-drawn imprecision
2. **Stroke Consistency** - All strokes intentional and uniform (2-3px primary, 1.5px secondary)
3. **Color Fidelity** - Exact hex codes from palette, WCAG AA contrast verified
4. **Scalability Tested** - Verified clear at 0.5", 1", 2", 6", 24" with no detail loss
5. **Visual Hierarchy** - Single focal point with clear primary/secondary/tertiary elements

### Mandatory Deliverables (Per Concept)
- [ ] Full color vector (.SVG, layered)
- [ ] Monochrome version (proves works without color)
- [ ] Inverted version (white on dark background)
- [ ] Scale verification image (all 5 sizes side-by-side)
- [ ] 4 Context mockups: website header, business card, social media, event poster
- [ ] Design rationale document (2-3 paragraphs + reference to pillars)

### Quality Gate Before Stakeholder Presentation
Must pass `PRODUCTION_DESIGN_STANDARDS.md` Design Review Checklist:
- ‚úÖ Precision verification (no geometry errors)
- ‚úÖ Consistency review (colors, strokes, spacing)
- ‚úÖ Scalability testing (all 5 sizes verified)
- ‚úÖ Accessibility review (contrast, colorblind, monochrome)
- ‚úÖ Brand alignment (pillars supported, distinctive, professional)

**Reference:** See `PRODUCTION_DESIGN_STANDARDS.md` for complete standards documentation, examples of production vs. immature design, and quality checklist.

